			<div class="mt-3">
				<h5 class="offcanvas-title text-primary">Drawing register - relevant idea?</h5>
				<br />
				<p class="text-secondary">
					&emsp;Do industrial companies need an app like this? The answer should be yes and no. The idea of storing all 
					your drawings on the web seems exciting and frightening. From my 10 years of experience as a design engineer, 
					<strong>I could highly suggest using some king of drawing register</strong>.<br />&emsp;Working with drawing files scattered in 
					your business server is a very bad idea - nobody knows where the most recent drawing revision is or where the 
					drawings are at all. Usually, engineers try to store files in their own pattern and according to their own habits, 
					and that's what confuses the whole company.
				</p>
				<div class="mt-2 mb-2 text-end">
					<a href="#top" class="text-primary">(back to top)</a>
				</div>
			</div>

			<br />
			<div id="roles" class="mt-3">

				<h5 class="offcanvas-title text-primary">Roles</h5>
				<br />
				<p class="text-secondary">
					&emsp;Drawing register relies on Microsoft Identity Roles. Simple implementation drew me in. This simple aplication references roles nearly 200 times:
				</p>
				<pre><label>CSHTML</label><code>@HomeCodeSnipits.roleCSHTML</code></pre>
				<pre><label>C#</label><code>@HomeCodeSnipits.role1Csharp</code></pre>
				<p class="text-secondary">
					&emsp;It is a time-saving solution that is easy to over complicate: changing roles while user is logged in makes 
					its claims out of date. Controllers constantly must update user claims. I don't know if this is a good practice, 
					but it's working smoothly so far:
				</p>
				<pre><label>C#</label><code>@HomeCodeSnipits.role2Csharp</code></pre>
				<p class="text-secondary">&emsp;The register has five principal roles:</p>
				<div class="row row-cols-md-auto justify-content-around">
					<div class="card border-light col mb-3" style="max-width: 15rem; min-width: 10rem">
						<div class="card-header"><img style="height:2em" src="~/Assets/user.png" /></div>
						<div class="card-body">
							<h4 class="card-title text-secondary">NormalUser</h4>
							<p class="card-text text-secondary">Global role: modify password, delete account, create invitation request, create register. Assign for each new user.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="card border-light col mb-3" style="max-width: 15rem; min-width: 10rem">
						<div class="card-header"><img style="height:2em" src="~/Assets/owner.png" /></div>
						<div class="card-body">
							<h4 class="card-title text-secondary">Administrator</h4>
							<p class="card-text text-secondary">Register role: All CRUD operations. Assign during register creation or by another administrator.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="card border-light col mb-3" style="max-width: 15rem; min-width: 10rem">
						<div class="card-header"><img style="height:2em" src="~/Assets/engineer.png" /></div>
						<div class="card-body">
							<h4 class="card-title text-secondary">Engineer</h4>
							<p class="card-text text-secondary">Register role: All CRUD operations on valid project states. Assign during invitation or by administrator.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="card border-light col mb-3" style="max-width: 15rem; min-width: 10rem">
						<div class="card-header"><img style="height:2em" src="~/Assets/mechanic.png" /></div>
						<div class="card-body">
							<h4 class="card-title text-secondary">Mechanic</h4>
							<p class="card-text text-secondary">Register role: Limited to read on valid project states. Assign during invitation or by administrator.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="card border-light col mb-3" style="max-width: 15rem; min-width: 10rem">
						<div class="card-header"><img style="height:2em" src="~/Assets/spectator.png" /></div>
						<div class="card-body">
							<h4 class="card-title text-secondary">Spectator</h4>
							<p class="card-text text-secondary">App built in role: Limited to read operations only. Doesn't have any other roles, can't be assigned.</p>
						</div>
					</div>

				</div>
				<div class="mt-2 mb-2 text-end">
					<a href="#top" class="text-primary">(back to top)</a>
				</div>

			</div>
			<br />
			<div id="files" class="mt-3">

				<h5 class="offcanvas-title text-primary">Files</h5>
				<br />
